<heading id="D08681B6FFE3FFAB24FBF9D2FDE8F9B1" bold="true" box="[151,530,1605,1631]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" reason="1">
<taxonomicName id="4C714D59FFE3FFAB24FBF9D2FDE8F9B1" authority="Garsault, 1764" authorityName="Garsault" authorityYear="1764" box="[151,530,1605,1631]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Lacertus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE3FFAB24FBF9D2FDE8F9B1" bold="true" box="[151,530,1605,1631]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE3FFAB24FBF9D2FEA9F9B1" bold="true" box="[151,339,1605,1631]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Lacertus viridis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE04B2BFFE3FFAB2536F9D2FDE8F9B1" author="Garsault" box="[346,530,1605,1631]" pageId="25" pageNumber="40" refString="Garsault, F. A. P. de (1764) Les Figures des plantes et animaux d'usage en medecine, decrits dans la Matiere Medicale de Mr. Geoffroy Medecin. Paris, [i - v] + 1 - 20, pl. 644 - 729." type="book chapter" year="1764">
Garsault, 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE3FFAB25BBF9D2FDE8F9B1" box="[471,530,1605,1631]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1764.0">1764</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCE36DAFFE3FFAB24FBF91FFDF5F86C" blockId="25.[151,1436,1672,1959]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
The plate 
<quantity id="4C899B3FFFE3FFAB2560F91FFEADF94C" box="[268,343,1672,1698]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.69926" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" unit="in" value="669.0">669 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE04B2BFFE3FFAB2532F91FFDECF94C" author="Garsault" box="[350,534,1672,1698]" pageId="25" pageNumber="40" refString="Garsault, F. A. P. de (1764) Les Figures des plantes et animaux d'usage en medecine, decrits dans la Matiere Medicale de Mr. Geoffroy Medecin. Paris, [i - v] + 1 - 20, pl. 644 - 729." type="book chapter" year="1764">
Garsault (
<number id="3DB924FDFFE3FFAB25BDF91FFDF4F94C" box="[465,526,1672,1698]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1764.0">1764</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
shows his 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D59FFE3FFAB26F5F91FFCA8F94F" authority="Lacepède, 1788" authorityName="Lacepède" authorityYear="1788" box="[665,850,1672,1697]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Lacertus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE3FFAB26F5F91FFCA8F94F" box="[665,850,1672,1697]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Lacertus viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or “Lézard verd”, which is undoubtedly a species of the group of 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D59FFE3FFAB253EF939FD31F929" authority="Laurenti, 1768" authorityName="Laurenti" authorityYear="1768" box="[338,715,1709,1735]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Lacerta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE3FFAB253EF939FDF8F929" box="[338,514,1710,1735]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Lacerta viridis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE04B2BFFE3FFAB267DF93AFD38F929" author="Laurenti" box="[529,706,1709,1735]" pageId="25" pageNumber="42" refString="Laurenti, J. N. (1768) Specimen medicum, exhibens synopsin Reptilium emendatam cum experimentis circa venena et antidota Reptilium austriacorum. Viennae, Joan. Thom. Nob. de Trattnern, i - ii + 1 - 215, pl. 1 - 5." type="book chapter" year="1768">
Laurenti, 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE3FFAB26EAF93AFD38F929" box="[646,706,1709,1735]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1768.0">1768</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(family 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D59FFE3FFAB275FF939FB9FF929" authority="Batsch, 1788" authorityName="Batsch" authorityYear="1788" box="[819,1125,1709,1735]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE3FFAB275FF939FC3BF929" box="[819,961,1710,1735]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">LACERTIDAE</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE04B2BFFE3FFAB27A5F93AFB9FF929" author="Batsch" box="[969,1125,1709,1735]" pageId="25" pageNumber="36" refString="Batsch, A. J. G. C. (1788) Versuch einer Anleitung, zur Kennniss und Geschichte der Thiere und Mineralien. Erster Theil. Jena, Akademischen Buchhandlung, i - viii + 1 - 528, pl. 1 - 5." type="book chapter" year="1788">
Batsch, 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE3FFAB2045F93AFB9FF929" box="[1065,1125,1709,1735]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1788.0">1788</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
). However, if we suppose that the specimens drawn by Garsault were from the Paris region or at least from 
<collectingCountry id="F366764AFFE3FFAB20ECF945FB28F902" box="[1152,1234,1746,1772]" name="France" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">France</collectingCountry>
(see above), the specimen of plate 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE3FFAB2516F96FFE52F8FC" box="[378,424,1784,1810]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="669.0">669</number>
could not be a 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D59FFE3FFAB2604F96FFCE5F8FF" box="[616,799,1784,1809]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Lacerta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE3FFAB2604F96FFCE5F8FF" box="[616,799,1784,1809]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Lacerta viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but must have belonged in the species now named 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D59FFE3FFAB24FBF889FDF7F8D9" authority="Daudin, 1802" authorityName="Daudin" authorityYear="1802" box="[151,525,1821,1847]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Lacerta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bilineata">
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE3FFAB24FBF889FE98F8D9" box="[151,354,1822,1847]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Lacerta bilineata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE04B2BFFE3FFAB2506F88AFDF7F8D9" author="Daudin" box="[362,525,1821,1847]" pageId="25" pageNumber="37" refString="Daudin, F. M. (1802) Histoire naturelle, generale et particuliere des reptiles. Tome troisieme. Paris, F. Dufart, 1 - 452, pl. 29 - 45." type="book chapter" year="1802">
Daudin, 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE3FFAB25BCF88AFDF7F8D9" box="[464,525,1821,1847]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1802.0">1802</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, a nomen formerly considered a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D59FFE3FFAB2049F889FA61F8D9" authority="Laurenti, 1768" authorityName="Laurenti" authorityYear="1768" box="[1061,1435,1821,1847]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Lacerta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE3FFAB2049F889FB29F8D9" box="[1061,1235,1822,1847]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Lacerta viridis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE04B2BFFE3FFAB208FF88AFA6EF8D9" author="Laurenti" box="[1251,1428,1821,1847]" pageId="25" pageNumber="42" refString="Laurenti, J. N. (1768) Specimen medicum, exhibens synopsin Reptilium emendatam cum experimentis circa venena et antidota Reptilium austriacorum. Viennae, Joan. Thom. Nob. de Trattnern, i - ii + 1 - 215, pl. 1 - 5." type="book chapter" year="1768">
Laurenti, 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE3FFAB2134F88AFA6EF8D9" box="[1368,1428,1821,1847]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1768.0">1768</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(e.g. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE04B2BFFE3FFAB24B8F8D5FDEEF8B2" author="Mertens" box="[212,532,1858,1884]" pageId="25" pageNumber="43" refString="Mertens, R. &amp; Wermuth, H. (1960) Die Amphibien und Reptilien Europas. Dritte Liste, nach dem Stand vom 1. Januar 1960. Frankfurt am Main, Waldemar Kramer, i - xi, 1 - 264." type="journal article" year="1960">
Mertens &amp; Wermuth 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE3FFAB25B8F8D5FDEEF8B2" box="[468,532,1858,1884]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1960.0">1960</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE3FFAB264CF8D5FDB4F8B2" box="[544,590,1858,1884]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="151.0">151</number>
) but now considered to apply to a distinct species, the “western green lizard” (see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE04B2BFFE3FFAB2548F8FFFDFAF86C" author="Amann" box="[292,512,1896,1922]" pageId="25" pageNumber="35" refString="Amann, T., Rykena, S., Joger, U., Nettmann, H. K. &amp; Veith, M. (1997) Zur artlichen Trennung von Lacerta bilineata Daudin, 1802 und L. viridis (Laurenti, 1768). Salamandra, 33 (4), 255 - 268." type="journal article" year="1997">
Amann 
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE3FFAB25EEF8FFFE47F86F" box="[386,445,1896,1921]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">et al.</emphasis>
<number id="3DB924FDFFE3FFAB25A8F8FFFDFAF86C" box="[452,512,1896,1922]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1997.0">1997</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36B6551FFE3FFAB24AAF81AFC30F81E" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCE36DAFFE3FFAB24AAF81AFA66F849" blockId="25.[151,1436,1672,1959]" box="[198,1436,1933,1959]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
The nomen 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D59FFE3FFAB2539F819FD3CF849" authority="Garsault, 1764" authorityName="Garsault" authorityYear="1764" box="[341,710,1933,1959]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Lacertus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE3FFAB2539F819FDF5F849" box="[341,527,1934,1959]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Lacertus viridis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE04B2BFFE3FFAB2674F81AFD3CF849" author="Garsault" box="[536,710,1933,1959]" pageId="25" pageNumber="40" refString="Garsault, F. A. P. de (1764) Les Figures des plantes et animaux d'usage en medecine, decrits dans la Matiere Medicale de Mr. Geoffroy Medecin. Paris, [i - v] + 1 - 20, pl. 644 - 729." type="book chapter" year="1764">
Garsault, 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE3FFAB26E7F81AFD3CF849" box="[651,710,1933,1959]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1764.0">1764</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is a senior asthenomonym (secondary homonym) of 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D59FFE3FFAB212DF819FA66F849" box="[1345,1436,1934,1959]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Lacerta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE3FFAB212DF819FA66F849" box="[1345,1436,1934,1959]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Lacerta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCE36DAFFE3FFAB24FBF84EFC30F81E" blockId="25.[151,970,2009,2033]" box="[151,970,2009,2033]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<number id="3DB924FDFFE3FFAB24FBF84EFF5DF81E" box="[151,167,2009,2032]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="2.0">2</number>
. For the valid author and date of this family nomen, see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE04B2BFFE3FFAB2770F84EFC3CF81E" author="Dubois" box="[796,966,2009,2033]" pageId="25" pageNumber="38" refString="Dubois, A. (2004 a) The higher nomenclature of recent amphibians. Alytes, 22 (1 - 2), 1 - 14." type="journal article" year="2004" yearSuffix="a">
Dubois (
<number id="3DB924FDFFE3FFAB271BF84EFC54F81E" box="[887,942,2009,2032]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="2004.0">2004</number>
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE3FFAB27C1F84DFC40F81F" box="[941,954,2010,2033]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">a</emphasis>
)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36B6551FFE0FFA824FBFF0FFD1DFD0C" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8BCE36DAFFE0FFA824FBFF0FFD1DFD0C" blockId="26.[151,1437,152,738]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<taxonomicName id="4C714D59FFE0FFA824FBFF0FFE55FF5C" authority="Laurenti, 1768" authorityName="Laurenti" authorityYear="1768" box="[151,431,152,178]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Lacertus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE0FFA824FBFF0FFF19FF5F" box="[151,227,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">viridis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE04B2BFFE0FFA8249EFF0FFE5CFF5C" author="Laurenti" box="[242,422,152,178]" pageId="26" pageNumber="42" refString="Laurenti, J. N. (1768) Specimen medicum, exhibens synopsin Reptilium emendatam cum experimentis circa venena et antidota Reptilium austriacorum. Viennae, Joan. Thom. Nob. de Trattnern, i - ii + 1 - 215, pl. 1 - 5." type="book chapter" year="1768">
Laurenti, 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE0FFA8250BFF0FFE5CFF5C" box="[359,422,152,178]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" value="1768.0">1768</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, originally described as a member of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D59FFE0FFA8278BFF0FFB22FF5C" authority="Laurenti, 1768" authorityName="Laurenti" authorityYear="1768" box="[999,1240,152,178]" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Seps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE0FFA8278BFF0FFBE7FF5F" box="[999,1053,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Seps</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE04B2BFFE0FFA82049FF0FFB22FF5C" author="Laurenti" box="[1061,1240,152,178]" pageId="26" pageNumber="42" refString="Laurenti, J. N. (1768) Specimen medicum, exhibens synopsin Reptilium emendatam cum experimentis circa venena et antidota Reptilium austriacorum. Viennae, Joan. Thom. Nob. de Trattnern, i - ii + 1 - 215, pl. 1 - 5." type="book chapter" year="1768">
Laurenti, 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE0FFA820F5FF0FFB22FF5C" box="[1177,1240,152,178]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" value="1768.0">1768</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Its allocation to the species now known as 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D59FFE0FFA8258BFF2AFD3BFF38" box="[487,705,189,214]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Lacerta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bilineata">
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE0FFA8258BFF2AFD3BFF38" box="[487,705,189,214]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Lacerta bilineata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
would require that another nomen be given to the species currently known as 
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE0FFA825E9FF75FDC4FF15" box="[389,574,226,251]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<taxonomicName id="4C714D59FFE0FFA825E9FF75FDC0FF15" box="[389,570,226,251]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Lacerta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="viridis">Lacerta viridis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
According to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE04B2BFFE0FFA82680FF75FB80FF12" author="Mertens" box="[748,1146,226,252]" pageId="26" pageNumber="43" refString="Mertens, R. &amp; Wermuth, H. (1960) Die Amphibien und Reptilien Europas. Dritte Liste, nach dem Stand vom 1. Januar 1960. Frankfurt am Main, Waldemar Kramer, i - xi, 1 - 264." type="journal article" year="1960">
Mertens &amp; Wermuth (
<number id="3DB924FDFFE0FFA8279FFF75FBCEFF12" box="[1011,1076,226,252]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" value="1960.0">1960</number>
: 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE0FFA8202DFF75FB8BFF12" box="[1089,1137,226,252]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" value="151.0">151</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, the first three available junior doxisonyms of the latter are three nomina created by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE04B2BFFE0FFA82723FE9FFBA5FECC" author="Laurenti" box="[847,1119,264,290]" pageId="26" pageNumber="42" refString="Laurenti, J. N. (1768) Specimen medicum, exhibens synopsin Reptilium emendatam cum experimentis circa venena et antidota Reptilium austriacorum. Viennae, Joan. Thom. Nob. de Trattnern, i - ii + 1 - 215, pl. 1 - 5." type="book chapter" year="1768">
Laurenti (
<number id="3DB924FDFFE0FFA827AEFE9FFBF8FECC" box="[962,1026,264,290]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" value="1768.0">1768</number>
: 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE0FFA82060FE9FFBADFECC" box="[1036,1111,264,290]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" value="61.5" valueMax="62.0" valueMin="61.0">61–62</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
for species that he referred to his genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D59FFE0FFA82547FEBAFE9AFEA8" authority="Laurenti, 1768" authorityName="Laurenti" authorityYear="1768" box="[299,352,301,326]" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Seps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE0FFA82547FEBAFE9AFEA8" box="[299,352,301,326]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Seps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, now an invalid junior doxisonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D59FFE0FFA82772FEBAFABAFEA9" authority="Linnaeus, 1758 (Stejneger 1936: 138)" authorityName="Linnaeus, 1758 (Stejneger" authorityPageNumber="138" authorityYear="1936" box="[798,1344,301,327]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Lacerta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE0FFA82772FEBAFC83FEA8" box="[798,889,301,326]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Lacerta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE04B2BFFE0FFA827ECFEBAFBCCFEA9" author="Linnaeus" box="[896,1078,301,327]" pageId="26" pageNumber="42" refString="Linnaeus, C. (1758) Systema Naturae per regna tria naturae, secundum classes, ordines, genera, species, cum characteribus, differentiis, synonymis, locis. Editio decima, reformata. Tomus I. Holmiae, Laurentii Salvii, [i - iv] + 1 - 824." type="book chapter" year="1758">
Linnaeus, 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE0FFA82797FEBAFBCCFEA9" box="[1019,1078,301,327]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" value="1758.0">1758</number>
</bibRefCitation>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE04B2BFFE0FFA82029FEBAFACDFEA9" author="Stejneger" box="[1093,1335,301,327]" pageId="26" pageNumber="45" refString="Stejneger, L. (1936) Types of the amphibian and reptilian genera proposed by Laurenti in 1768. Copeia, 1936 (3), 133 - 141." type="journal article" year="1936">
Stejneger 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE0FFA820D1FEBAFB06FEA9" box="[1213,1276,301,327]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" value="1936.0">1936</number>
: 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE0FFA8216BFEBAFACDFEA9" box="[1287,1335,301,327]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" value="138.0">138</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Acting as First-Revisers, we hereby choose the following order of priority among these three nomina: 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D59FFE0FFA8217EFEC5FEB4FE7C" authority="Laurenti, 1768" authorityName="Laurenti" authorityYear="1768" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Seps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="varius">
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE0FFA8217EFEC5FA66FE85" box="[1298,1436,338,363]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Seps varius</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE04B2BFFE0FFA824FBFEEFFEB4FE7C" author="Laurenti" box="[151,334,376,402]" pageId="26" pageNumber="42" refString="Laurenti, J. N. (1768) Specimen medicum, exhibens synopsin Reptilium emendatam cum experimentis circa venena et antidota Reptilium austriacorum. Viennae, Joan. Thom. Nob. de Trattnern, i - ii + 1 - 215, pl. 1 - 5." type="book chapter" year="1768">
Laurenti, 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE0FFA82562FEEFFEB4FE7C" box="[270,334,376,402]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" value="1768.0">1768</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, then 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D59FFE0FFA825F4FEEFFD06FE7C" authority="Laurenti, 1768" authorityName="Laurenti" authorityYear="1768" box="[408,764,376,402]" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Seps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sericeus">
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE0FFA825F4FEEFFDC6FE7F" box="[408,572,376,401]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Seps sericeus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE04B2BFFE0FFA82628FEEFFD06FE7C" author="Laurenti" box="[580,764,376,402]" pageId="26" pageNumber="42" refString="Laurenti, J. N. (1768) Specimen medicum, exhibens synopsin Reptilium emendatam cum experimentis circa venena et antidota Reptilium austriacorum. Viennae, Joan. Thom. Nob. de Trattnern, i - ii + 1 - 215, pl. 1 - 5." type="book chapter" year="1768">
Laurenti, 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE0FFA826D0FEEFFD06FE7C" box="[700,764,376,402]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" value="1768.0">1768</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, then 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D59FFE0FFA8272AFEEFFB4FFE7C" authority="Laurenti, 1768" authorityName="Laurenti" authorityYear="1768" box="[838,1205,376,402]" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Seps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="terrestris">
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE0FFA8272AFEEFFC0FFE7F" box="[838,1013,376,401]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Seps terrestris</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE04B2BFFE0FFA82791FEEFFB4FFE7C" author="Laurenti" box="[1021,1205,376,402]" pageId="26" pageNumber="42" refString="Laurenti, J. N. (1768) Specimen medicum, exhibens synopsin Reptilium emendatam cum experimentis circa venena et antidota Reptilium austriacorum. Viennae, Joan. Thom. Nob. de Trattnern, i - ii + 1 - 215, pl. 1 - 5." type="book chapter" year="1768">
Laurenti, 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE0FFA82018FEEFFB4FFE7C" box="[1140,1205,376,402]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" value="1768.0">1768</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Consequently, the species long known as 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D59FFE0FFA825CBFE0AFDAFFE58" box="[423,597,413,438]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Lacerta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE0FFA825CBFE0AFDAFFE58" box="[423,597,413,438]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Lacerta viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should now be known as 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D59FFE0FFA827E4FE0AFBD3FE58" box="[904,1065,413,438]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Lacerta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="varia">
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE0FFA827E4FE0AFBD3FE58" box="[904,1065,413,438]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Lacerta varia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and the nomen 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D59FFE0FFA82082FE0AFA66FE58" box="[1262,1436,413,438]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Lacerta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE0FFA82082FE0AFA66FE58" box="[1262,1436,413,438]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Lacerta viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should now apply to the species currently known as 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D59FFE0FFA8277FFE55FC19FE35" box="[787,995,450,475]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Lacerta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bilineata">
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE0FFA8277FFE55FC19FE35" box="[787,995,450,475]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Lacerta bilineata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We think this change would have a disruptive effect on communication among zoologists, as the nomen 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D59FFE0FFA827B6FE7FFB85FDEF" box="[986,1151,488,513]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Lacerta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="varia">
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE0FFA827B6FE7FFB85FDEF" box="[986,1151,488,513]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Lacerta varia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has never been used as valid, and as, since its creation and for about 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE0FFA826DAFD9AFD18FDC9" box="[694,738,525,551]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" value="250.0">250</number>
years, the nomen 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D59FFE0FFA827D1FD9AFB94FDC8" box="[957,1134,525,550]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Lacerta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE0FFA827D1FD9AFB94FDC8" box="[957,1134,525,550]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Lacerta viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been associated with the common green lizard present in most of Europe (for a list of more than 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE0FFA82055FDA5FBADFDA2" box="[1081,1111,562,588]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" value="25.0">25</number>
recent references, see e.g. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE04B2BFFE0FFA824FBFDCFFE1EFD9C" author="Nettmann" box="[151,484,600,626]" pageId="26" pageNumber="43" refString="Nettmann, H. - K. &amp; Rykena, S. (1984) Lacerta viridis (Laurenti, 1768) - Samaragdeidechse. In: W. Bohme (ed.), Handbuch der Reptilien und Amphibien Europas, Band 2 / I, Wiesbaden, Aula-Verlag, 129 - 180." type="book chapter" year="1984">
Nettmann &amp; Rykena 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE0FFA825CDFDCFFE1EFD9C" box="[417,484,600,626]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" value="1984.0">1984</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE0FFA8259CFDCFFD99FD9C" box="[496,611,600,626]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" value="176.5" valueMax="180.0" valueMin="173.0">173–180</number>
). We therefore use Article 23.9. 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE0FFA82795FDCFFBFEFD9C" box="[1017,1028,600,626]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" value="1.0">1</number>
of the 
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE0FFA82033FDCFFB5AFD9F" box="[1119,1184,600,625]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Code</emphasis>
to reject the nomen 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D59FFE0FFA824FBFDEAFDFCFD79" authority="Garsault, 1764" authorityName="Garsault" authorityYear="1764" box="[151,518,637,663]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Lacertus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE0FFA824FBFDEAFEABFD78" box="[151,337,637,662]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Lacertus viridis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE04B2BFFE0FFA82535FDEAFDFCFD79" author="Garsault" box="[345,518,637,663]" pageId="26" pageNumber="40" refString="Garsault, F. A. P. de (1764) Les Figures des plantes et animaux d'usage en medecine, decrits dans la Matiere Medicale de Mr. Geoffroy Medecin. Paris, [i - v] + 1 - 20, pl. 644 - 729." type="book chapter" year="1764">
Garsault, 
<quantity id="4C899B3FFFE0FFA825A7FDEAFDFCFD79" box="[459,518,637,663]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.48056" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" unit="in" value="1764.0">1764</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in favour of its junior asthenomonym 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D59FFE0FFA827A3FDEAFAB0FD79" authority="Laurenti, 1768" authorityName="Laurenti" authorityYear="1768" box="[975,1354,637,663]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Lacerta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE0FFA827A3FDEAFB84FD78" box="[975,1150,637,662]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Lacerta viridis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE04B2BFFE0FFA820E1FDEAFABBFD79" author="Laurenti" box="[1165,1345,637,663]" pageId="26" pageNumber="42" refString="Laurenti, J. N. (1768) Specimen medicum, exhibens synopsin Reptilium emendatam cum experimentis circa venena et antidota Reptilium austriacorum. Viennae, Joan. Thom. Nob. de Trattnern, i - ii + 1 - 215, pl. 1 - 5." type="book chapter" year="1768">
Laurenti, 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE0FFA8216EFDEAFABBFD79" box="[1282,1345,637,663]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" value="1768.0">1768</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Being rejected under this Article, 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D59FFE0FFA825BBFD35FCBEFD52" authority="Garsault, 1764" authorityName="Garsault" authorityYear="1764" box="[471,836,674,700]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Lacertus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE0FFA825BBFD35FD6AFD55" box="[471,656,674,699]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Lacertus viridis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE04B2BFFE0FFA826FBFD35FCBEFD52" author="Garsault" box="[663,836,674,700]" pageId="26" pageNumber="40" refString="Garsault, F. A. P. de (1764) Les Figures des plantes et animaux d'usage en medecine, decrits dans la Matiere Medicale de Mr. Geoffroy Medecin. Paris, [i - v] + 1 - 20, pl. 644 - 729." type="book chapter" year="1764">
Garsault, 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE0FFA82765FD35FCBEFD52" box="[777,836,674,700]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" value="1764.0">1764</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
becomes an exoplonym and it does not threaten its junior doxisonym 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D59FFE0FFA82502FD5FFD19FD0C" authority="Daudin, 1802" authorityName="Daudin" authorityYear="1802" box="[366,739,712,738]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Lacerta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bilineata">
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE0FFA82502FD5FFDC2FD0F" box="[366,568,712,737]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Lacerta bilineata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE04B2BFFE0FFA8262CFD5FFD19FD0C" author="Daudin" box="[576,739,712,738]" pageId="26" pageNumber="37" refString="Daudin, F. M. (1802) Histoire naturelle, generale et particuliere des reptiles. Tome troisieme. Paris, F. Dufart, 1 - 452, pl. 29 - 45." type="book chapter" year="1802">
Daudin, 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE0FFA826C9FD5FFD19FD0C" box="[677,739,712,738]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" value="1802.0">1802</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
